        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian" method="pen">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Vna Vncia co[n]tinet charattos 144:   
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>One twelfth contains 144 carats.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian" method="pen">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Qua[n]titate[m] vtrimsq[ue] Metalli h&icirc;c co[m]mixti semper supponit esse Marcam, id est, vncias octo: scilicet charattos 1152. 
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                He supposes that quantity of both metals mixed here always is a mark [=a measure of weight], that is, 8/12, which is, naturally, 1152 carats. <!--JG: Very unsure-->
            </translation>
